Once upon a time, in the magical land of JavaScript, there lived a clever wizard named Merlin who had a magical spell to find the sum of all numbers in an array. Let me share his spell with you:

```javascript
// The array of numbers
const numbers = [1, 2, 3, 4, 5];

// A magical function cast by Wizard Merlin to find the sum of all numbers in the array
function findSumOfNumbers(numbers) {
    let sum = 0;
    for (let number of numbers) {
        sum += number;
    }
    return sum;
}

// Casting the spell to find the sum of all numbers in the array
const sum = findSumOfNumbers(numbers);

// Displaying the magical result
console.log(`The sum of all numbers in the array is: ${sum}`);
```

And just like that, with a flick of his wand and a few lines of code, Wizard Merlin was able to find the sum of all numbers in the array. The villagers were amazed by his magical powers and the simplicity of his spell. And so, the legend of Wizard Merlin and his sum-finding spell was passed down from generation to generation in the land of JavaScript.
